Implement support for embedded maps in Entity classes, both of structured and (datastore) primitive types. Maps can only be keyed by strings, and the keys cannot contain dots ('.'). Map entries are stored with the map field name and the map entry key as their prefix. As paths are no longer fixed, we need to pass around a path during saving, and we need to search a suitable map during loading. After finding a map field, the map setter uses a nested Transmog to further dispatch and load the field. This makes nested maps possible.
